WEBVTT

00:02:29.572 --> 00:02:31.061
anywhere in the United States.

00:02:31.681 --> 00:02:34.624
And you would think growing up
in a place like New York,

00:02:34.648 --> 00:02:38.233
it would be easy for a first-generation
person to find their place.

00:02:38.947 --> 00:02:41.129
But all throughout my childhood,

00:02:41.153 --> 00:02:44.583
there were these moments
that formed my understanding

00:02:44.607 --> 00:02:46.578
of the different worlds I belonged to.

00:02:47.522 --> 00:02:50.341
When I was in the fifth grade,
a student asked me

00:02:50.365 --> 00:02:52.719
if my family was refugees.

00:02:53.386 --> 00:02:55.180
I didn't know what that word meant.

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:57.942
He explained to me
that his parents told him

00:02:57.966 --> 00:03:01.986
that refugees are people from Africa
who come to the US